sion, the economy at large. The contributors to this thoughtful volume examine the current state of prudential supervision, focusing on fundamental issues and key pragmatic concerns. Why is prudential supervision so important? What kinds of excess must it guard against? What particular forms does it take? Which of these are the most effective deterrents against mismanagement and system overload in today's rapidly shifting financial climate? The contributors foresee a continued movement beyond simple regulatory rules in banking and toward a more active evaluation and supervision of a bank's risk management practices.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBank managementvCongresses. 0aBanks and bankingxGovernment policyvCongresses. 0aRisk managementvCongresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aBarth, James R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerger, Allen N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBliss, Robert R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalomiris, Charles W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaprio, Gerard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarey, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCecchetti, Stephen G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlannery, Mark J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGertler, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKroszner, Randall S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKyle, Margaret K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevine, Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1